  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "A century after Hubris, Eisenhorn is hunted by his own kind. Quixos, a fellow Inquisitor turned radical, has bound himself to a daemonic patron and accuses Eisenhorn of heresy to deflect attention from his own pact-making. Eisenhorn flees Inquisitorial detention with his small retinue and crosses Gudrun, Sameter and the daemon-touched world of Eechan in pursuit of evidence. To beat Quixos he risks bargaining with a chained daemonhost named Cherubael — bitter, lucid, and almost certainly listening too closely. The novel closes on the doctrine of the Tyrantine Cabal — the radical Inquisitorial subset who hold that the Emperor's Tarot must be read against the grain — and Eisenhorn keeps a copy of his bargain in writing, against the day the bargain itself reads him.",
